= Redmine Markdown Extra formatter

This is a redmine plugin for supporting Markdown Extra as a wiki format.

== What is redmine?
Redmine is a flexible project management web application.
See ((<the official site|URL:http://www.redmine.org>)) for more details.

== What is Markdown Extra?
(from http://michelf.com/projects/php-markdown/extra/)
PHP Markdown Extra is a special version of PHP Markdown implementing some
features currently not available with the plain Markdown syntax.


== Plugin installation
=== Prerequisites
* Redmine and its prerequisites
* bluefeather gem - see http://ruby.morphball.net/bluefeather/

=== Installation
(1) Copy the plugin directory into the vendor/plugins directory
(2) Start Redmine

Installed plugins are listed on 'Admin -> Information' screen.

=== Credits
